Column Attributes
    Open a table in design mode. We have different columns:
    
    ColumnName: Just the name assigned to that column
    Datatype(NUM): Just the type of data assigned to that column. NUM represent the maximum of that data type.
                   we have:
                    INT=> hold number 
                    VARCHAR => Variable Character(save space dynamically)
                    CHAR =>  Character(Waste space unnecesary)
                    DATE => for date time, become with standard space(fixed)
    PK: Mark the column as the Primary Key
    NN: Determinates if the column can't accept Not values or Null
        if we dont check a column, means the column is optional(can accept null values)
    AI: Often use with PK column, means Auto Increment. Everytime we insert a new record, we let MySQL 
        insert a value in this column(see the last value e.x customer_id and set +1)
    Default/Expression: Specify the default value for each column. Often(Not always) used when we mark columns as optionals(NN)
                        so we specify default values. e.x NULL, '0'

    
